      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TYSON NZ (2) made an encouraging start in Queensland when runner-up at this circuit. has won a trial since then so should have come on and is aided by a good draw. ARKIN WICKED (1) had to call on all reserves to salute at the most recent appearance over 2138m at this track, getting home by just a neck. Won't find this any harder and he can go right on with the job. TARGARYEN NZ (7) missed the placings two runs back then did a great job to finish 5 metres back in third despite breaking in the run over 2138m at this circuit a week ago. Live chance again in a similar assignment. MOSSDALE TERRY NZ (8) broke last start and finished 6 metres from the winner in fourth over 2138m at this venue. That followed a ninth to launch this prep. Meets a similar line up so if he behaves a big run is likely.",
